Description: CVE-2026-32814 - Initialize allocated memory to avoid information leak
 libheif allocates canvas plane memory without zero-initialization. When grid
 tile decoding fails with strict_decoding=false (default), uninitialized heap
 memory can be exposed as pixel data. This patch changes the allocation from
 new[] to calloc() to ensure all memory is zero-initialized, preventing
 information leakage.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/strukturag/libheif/commit/6aca89d76a5118bd47adcb5b83e7b01a32134985
Author: Dirk Farin <dirk.farin@gmail.com>
